Hi team, it seems that the Confluence PDF preview sometimes omits content such as images, as you can see in the attached screenshot, and sometimes text. Visitors who see these incompletely-displayed PDFs sometimes completely fail to realize that content is missing, which can be disastrous. Or in the case of images, they sometimes believe that we've accidentally forgotten to include images, which makes us seem incompetent and unprofessional at worst, or at the very least not detail-oriented. Hence I've flagged this as a critical issue due to its business impacts, especially when text is missing.

