People who collaborate are usually diverse in respect to thinking, working, cultural background and technology used. While Confluence in general is a great tool for collaboration, it has a serious flaw when it comes to attachments. They can only be handled easily if they are Microsoft Office files AND if you use Microsoft Internet Explorer (Firefox WebDAV plugin is broken on some OSes and generally not exactly under heavy development, as some issues here show). This poses severe restrictions for daily usage in a collaborative environment which can cause serious obstacles regarding productivity and generally frustrates people.

Therefore, I want to make the following suggestion to improve Confluence:

A user should be able to open any attachment via his browser directly within the appropiate application. This should be possible regardless of browser or OS used (at least on a classical desktop OS like Windows, Mac OS X or Linux) and regardless of file type or application involvled (as long as the user has an application installed that can handle a particular file type).

